<item>
            <title>[JAMES-1900] Decode headers before indexing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JAMES-1900</link>
                <project id="10411" key="JAMES">James Server</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Headers in emails are usually encoded using &lt;a href=&quot;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2047&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2047&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
It&apos;s the so-called encoded-word encoding.&lt;br/&gt;
When we put emails into ES, we should decode headers to UTF-8 to make sure search will match even non-ascii characters.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
